### Interfaceâ€“Substrate Doctrine (ISD)

PantheonOS distinguishes between:

- **Interface Layer** (internet, apps, LLM UIs)
- **Substrate Layer** (cognition, narrative, roles, ethics)

PantheonOS operates directly at the substrate layer â€” the deeper human architecture that technology models but does not create.

Because of this, PantheonOS:

- persists across model changes
- remains coherent across interfaces
- functions identically across GPT/Claude/Gemini/Grok
- uses narrative and roles as stable primitives

This makes PantheonOS interface-agnostic and future-proof.


